            Nina Mufti, Ph.D., was promoted to Vice President, Development at Cerus Corporation in 2012. Since 2007, she has guided the product design and development efforts for the INTERCEPT RBC System. Prior to Cerus, Dr. Mufti worked at Nektar Therapeutics on the development of drug and device combination products.Â  Dr. Mufti completed her Ph.D. in Biochemical Engineering at Cornell University, and her Bachelor of Science, Biochemistry and Bachelor of Applied Science, Chemical Engineering at University of Ottawa.









